text.Taxonomy and naming:
Boronia pilosa was first formally described in 1805 by Jacques Labillardière who published the description in  Novae Hollandiae Plantarum Specimen. The specific epithet (pilosa) is a Latin word meaning "hairy".In 2003, Marco Duretto described four subspecies:

Boronia pilosa subsp. parvidaemonis;
Boronia pilosa subsp. pilosa;
Boronia pilosa subsp. tasmanensis;
Boronia pilosa subsp. torquata.
